markdown: XV ANIVERSARIO DE LA DIVISION DE NUTRICION <::A circular logo for "INSTITUTO NACIONAL DE LA NUTRICION MEXICO". The outer ring of the logo contains the text "INSTITUTO NACIONAL DE LA NUTRICION MEXICO" in an arc, bordered by a decorative pattern resembling wheat or leaves. The inner part of the logo features a central image of a chemical flask or retort with a snake coiled around its base and body, reminiscent of the Rod of Asclepius. On the left side of the flask, there are wheat stalks and the curved text "nutritionis Scientia". On the right side, there are also wheat stalks and the curved text "populi Salus". Below the flask, there is a small, stylized symbol. The overall design suggests a blend of science, health, and nutrition.: figure::> ABSTRACTS OF PUBLICATIONS 1958-1972 INSTITUTO NACIONAL DE NUTRICION MEXICO·1972 Source: https://www.industrydocuments.ucsf.edu/docs/glby0228
